section.section:
The employer of an applicant for a commission shall:
submit to the Secretary an application on the form that the Secretary requires;
submit to the Secretary a complete set of the applicant's legible fingerprints on standard fingerprint cards;
pay to the Secretary a fee to cover the cost of the fingerprint record checks; and
subject to paragraph (3) of this subsection, pay to the Secretary an application fee of $100, to cover the cost of an investigation of the applicant.
